column1: NGR is Culmington Manor. Altitudes close maybe a bit high depending where the gauge is on the estate.

5 readings in the 1920s duplicate readings at the School, this is out 73 overlapping readings and may be suspicious particularly given that for the 3 years when the gauge was at the Rectory there are no duplicate readings.
1 reading in the 1930s duplicates  reading from Westhope Cottage, but there are 60 overlapping readings, therefore not suspicious
